a control system for logical block diagnosis with data loading.wthis paper describes a section of an integrateddiagnostic monitor system which facilitates the checking of sections of instructions or subroutinesanywhere in the object program.  a new method of specifying all diagnostic operations in a format similarto a computer program makes the system convenient to use and relatively simple to understand.  the paperalso describes a number of other novel diagnostic features which can be included in the system.cacm april, senko, m. e.ca jb march ,  : pm